Retrieve “all” NOTCH1 variants in PT_ZYKASPCW

Without knowing the specific chromosome/positions of this gene or the specific study this patient belongs to. (This is a request made by Allison as an example.)

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
participant_id = 'PT_ZYKASPCW'
gene_symbol = 'NOTCH1'
study_id = spark.sql("select study_id from participants where kf_id = '" + participant_id + "'").collect()[0]['study_id']
chr = spark.sql("select chromosome from human_genes where symbol='" + gene_symbol + "'").collect()[0]['chromosome']
c = spark.sql("select distinct chromosome, start, reference, alternate from consequences c where c.symbol='" + gene_symbol + "' and c.chromosome=" + chr)
o = spark.table('occurrences').alias('o')
o = o.where((o['chromosome'] == chr) & (o['study_id'] == study_id) & (o['participant_id'] == participant_id))
r = o.join(c, (o['chromosome'] == c['chromosome']) & (o['start'] == c['start']) & (o['reference'] == c['reference']) & (o['alternate'] == c['alternate']))
z.show(r.select('o.*'))

# Retrieve specific variants of interest in Kids First cohorts that I have access to
The following 7 variants are from Table 1 of the 2019 Nature Medicine [paper](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41591-019-0479-2) with PuBMed ID [31263281](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31263281/), see table below.
First I converted transcript-specific, HGVS-format variants (mutations) into chromosomal coordinates in hg38 using [Mutalyzer](https://www.mutalyzer.nl/), then generate notebook codes for variant lookup

(It seems the study `SD_BHJXBDQK` contains somatic variants from tumor DNA in CBTN)
